<p>
ANNEXURE 2<p>
<p>
<CENTER><b>ORISSA BRIEFING NOTE:</b><p>
<p>
Summary of Issues and Recommendations<p>
<p>
ICDS Non-formal
Pre-school
Component<p>
<p>
August 10, 1989<p>
<p>
Cassie Landers</center><p>
<p>

	The following report summarizes the discussions held:on August 10 with State
Government officials in Bhubaneshwar regarding the non-formal
child development component of ICDS. The report also reflects the comments from
a group of Anganwadi Workers (AWW) attending a refresher course at the Hose
Economics Training Centre. The issues and suggested programming
recommmendations emerging from these discussions are summarized in three
categories: A) State-level
Early Childhood Education Activities, B) AWW Training and Supervision, and C)
Field-level
Operations.<p>
<p>
	I would like to thank the State Government officials for their orientation and
hospitality, and for arranging my agenda on such short notice.<p>
<p>
	Particular thanks are due to the following individuals with whom I spoke
during my visit:<p>
<p>
	<ul>Department of Community Development and Rural Reconstruction<br>
	<ul>	R. B. Patnaik<br>
		J. K. Patnafk<br>
		Mr.Mohapatra<br>
		Gangadhar Naik</ul><p>
<p>
	SCERT<br>
	<ul>	Dr. P. C. Mishra</ul><p>
<p>
	Home Economics Training Centre<br>
	<ul>	Miss Bidyutlata Das</ul><p>
<p>
	UNICEF<br>
	<ul>	Mr. Gopi Menon</ul><p>
</ul><p>
	In addition, the discussion held at the Home Economics Training Centre with 50
AWW trainees from tribal areas was very enlightening.<p>
