<p>
<p>
In sum, based on the above data, it is apparent that about 40% of the preschool
aged children are in preschool centres, while only about 5% of those from birth
through 4 years of age are in some form of formal child care.  In both
instances, the centres are distributed throughout the country. <p>
<p>
The next question is, who is providing the ECD programmes?  Table 6 shows the
number of preschool centres that are supported by governmental, statutory,
private and social/religious institutions.  Clearly the predominant provider is
the government, with the private sector serving about 20% of those in
preschool.  These percentages have remained fairly constant over the time
period covered.<p>
<p>
<p>
