      3-5              34.6       31.8       29.5       25.4       24.1
      6 year olds      97.1       96.3       95.2       94.2       94.0
</pre>
<p>
<p>
	Beginning in 1991 there has been a distinct decrease in the number of children
going to preschool.  1990 was the year when such institutions were taken over
by communes, preschools run by enterprises were closed down, fees for preschool
education rose, and the decrease in the population meant there were fewer
children of preschool age. <p>
<p>
<center><b>Table 8<br>
