<HEAD>
<TITLE>
RAH96: About Industrial Smoke & Mirrors, Ltd.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/grph/rahbkgd.gif">
<CENTER>
<!-- Commonwealth Broadcasting Network HTML Code Version 3.0 -->
<a target=_top href=http://commonwealth.riddler.com/Commonwealth/bin/statthru?21174><img height=60 width=460 border=0 src=http://commonwealth.riddler.com/Commonwealth/bin/statdeploy?21174></a>
<BR>
<H3>
RAH96: About Industrial Smoke & Mirrors, Ltd.
</H3>
</CENTER>
<P>
Industrial Smoke & Mirrors, Ltd. is the former R&D division of Vaporware
Corporation that was sold off in February 1995 after the parent firm
declared bankruptcy.  Dr. Kung Pao Har Hoo, the former Vice President for
Research & Development with Vaporware Corporation, took over the newly
independent firm as President and CEO.
</P>
<P>
Industrial Smoke & Mirrors (ISM) is a world leader in totally useless
technological advances, trailing only Apple Computer in this area.
</P>
<P>
After a wildly successful ($2.2 billion) Initial Public Offering (IPO)
in February 1996 ISM had money for acquisitions. The firm spent nearly 
$200 million on pizza for all its programmers and scientists within 
the first month alone. This resulted in a great deal of work being 
accomplished, although a few folks had to be treated by paramedics for 
oregano and anchovy poisoning.
</P>
<P>
Things became even stickier soon thereafter when agents from the Securities 
and Exchange Commission began investigating the circumstances surrounding 
the ISM IPO. It seems that many investors had been attracted to the ISM 
offering by the words "Internet" and "World Wide Web" which appeared more 
than 200 times each in the prospectus. Nosy SEC agents soon ferreted out 
the minor detail that ISM's business had nothing whatsoever to do with the 
Internet or the Web. Dr. Hoo moved quickly in response to this revelation, 
making two critical hires.
</P>
<P>
Vinnie "The Knife" Calamari was hired as ISM Security Director, reprising
the role he played at Vaporware. Calamari's job will be to see that no
further investigative embarrassments befall ISM or its executives.
</P>
<P>
Dave Bealer, the former editor of <I>Random Access Humor</I>, the only
successful Vaporware venture other than ISM, was brought on board to run the 
new ISM Internet Division. Bealer spent the last year serving as editor and 
publisher of <I>Dream Forge - The Electronic Magazine For Your Mind</I>.
When asked about the change, Bealer said, "I really hate to leave a successful
venture like <I>Dream Forge</I>, but I just couldn't pass up the 
opportunity to work with Dr. Hoo and Vinnie again."
</P>
<P>
Bealer's first action upon taking the reins of the new ISM Internet 
Division was to begin work on <I>Random Access Humor 96</I>, the 
WWW-exclusive successor to <I>Random Access Humor</I>. Successful
efforts were made to secure the participation of such renowned RAH 
authors as Greg Borek.
</P>
<CENTER>
<P>
Industrial Smoke & Mirrors, Ltd.<BR>
32768 Infinite Loop<BR>
Sillycon Valley, CA. 80486-DX2<BR>
USA, Earth, Sol System, Milky Way<BR>
NASDAQ Symbol: SMIR
</P>
<P>
