of the web and is not affiliated with any specific network, ISP, or online
service.  RAH96 is a compilation of individual articles contributed by 
their authors.  The contribution of articles to this compilation does
not diminish the rights of the authors.  The opinions expressed in
RAH96 are those of the authors and are not necessarily those of the
editors, staff, publisher, or advertisers.
</P>
<P>
This entire publication is a work of satire (except for these legal
bits here).  If anyone takes offense to something published herein,
the fault (a lack of a sense of humor) lies with them and not with 
the magazine.  The editors and publisher will not be held responsible
for the use or misuse of any information contained in this magazine.
</P>
<P>
Random Access Humor 96 is Copyright 1996 Dave Bealer.  All Rights 
Reserved.  Unauthorized duplication and/or re-distribution is prohibited.
You may always point links from your site to the RAH96 site, or even to
particular articles. (Note that articles do change regularly, so those
kinds of links may break fairly quickly.) Copying an item from RAH96 to
your site is another matter entirely (a prohibited matter, in fact). The 
rights for individual articles remain with their authors. Obtain permission 
from the author <B>before</B> publishing, posting, or otherwise distributing
anything published in RAH96. If no author or copyright holder is specified 
for a particular item, contact the publisher for permission. The <B>only</B>
exception to this rule is for items that are specifically identified in
RAH96 as being public domain.
</P>
<P>
