<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
RAH96: Bumperstickers Seen On The Info Superhighway
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/grph/rahbkgd.gif">
<CENTER>
<!-- Commonwealth Broadcasting Network HTML Code Version 3.0 -->
<a target=_top href=http://commonwealth.riddler.com/Commonwealth/bin/statthru?214307><img height=60 width=460 border=0 src=http://commonwealth.riddler.com/Commonwealth/bin/statdeploy?214307></a>
<BR>
<H2>
<IMG SRC="/grph/rah96tm.gif" ALT="Random Access Humor 96 (TM)"><BR>
Bumperstickers Seen On The Info Superhighway
</H2>
<BR>
<P>
If I want your opinion, I'll ask you to fill out the necessary forms.
</P>
<P>
Don't look back, they might be gaining on you.
</P>
<P>
Shin -  a device for finding furniture in the dark.
</P>
<P>
Do witches use spell checkers?
</P>
<P>
Headline: Bear takes over Disneyland in Pooh d'etat!
</P>
<P>
2 + 2 = 5  for extremely large values of 2
</P>
<P>
Computers aren't intelligent, they only think they are.
</P>
<P>
My software never has bugs.  It just develops random features.
</P>
<P>
C:\WINDOWS  C:\WINDOWS\RUN  C:\PC\CRAWL
</P>
<P>
The name is Baud, James Baud.
</P>
<P>
BUFFERS=20  FILES=15  2nd down, 4th quarter, 5 yards to go
</P>
<P>
E Pluribus Modem
</P>
<P>
Mainframe - the largest available PC peripheral
</P>
<P>
Does fuzzy logic tickle?
</P>
<P>
A computer's attention span is only as long as its power cord.
</P>
<P>
Disinformation is not as good as datinformation.
</P>
<P>
Windows - just another pane in the glass.
</P>
<P>
Ultimate office automation - networked coffee.
</P>
<P>
Press any key... no, NOT THAT ONE! 
</P>
<P>
Excuse me for butting in, but I'm interrupt driven.
</P>
<P>
A fate <i>worse</i> than a fate worse than death? That sounds pretty bad.
- Lord Blackadder
</P>
<P>
Read my chips.  No new upgrades.
</P>
<P>
Programmer - a red-eyed, mumbling mammal capable of conversing with
inanimate objects.
</P>
<P>
People with no vices usually have annoying virtues.
</P>
<H3>
Taglines from the motion picture <i>Blazing Saddles</i>
</H3>
<P>
"To tell a family secret, my grandmother was Dutch." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Send a wire to the main office - tell them I said... 'ow!'"  - Taggart
</P>
<P>
"We've gotta protect our phoney-baloney jobs, gentlemen!" - Gov. Le Petomaine
</P>
<P>
"I didn't get a 'harrumph' out of that guy." - Gov. Le Petomaine
</P>
<P>
"Gentlemen, please, rest your sphincters." - Hedley Lamarr
</P>
<P>
Not to worry, everyone is equal in my eye." - The Executioner
</P>
<P>
"Excuse me while I whip this out." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Oh, baby, you are so talented. And they are so dumb." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Well, raise my rent! You are the kid." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"I must have killed more men than Cecil B. DeMille." - Jim
</P>
<P>
"The little bastard shot me in the ass." - Jim
</P>
<P>
"I always like to keep my audience riveted." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"These are... the common clay of the New West. You know, morons." - Jim
</P>
<P>
"Never mind that shit, here comes Mongo!" - somebody named Johnson
</P>
<P>
"Mongo ain't exact a 'who.' He's more of a 'what.'" - Jim
</P>
<P>
"Candygram for Mongo!" - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Let's face it, I'm tired!" - Lili Von Shtupp
</P>
<P>
"...them schintzengrubens can wipe you out." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Mongo only pawn in game of life." - Mongo
</P>
<P>
"They said you was hung." - Charlie  "...and they was right." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Alright, I'm through being Mr. Goodbar." - Hedley Lamarr
</P>
<P>
"Boy, is he strict!" - Jim
</P>
<P>
"And now, for my next impression, Jesse Owens." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"'Head them off at the pass?' I hate that cliche!" - Hedley Lamarr
</P>
<P>
"I got an idea that'll slow them down to a crawl." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Somebody's gotta go back and get a shitload of dimes!" - Taggart
</P>
<P>
"Piss on you! I'm workin' for Mel Brooks!" - Slim Pickens
</P>
<P>
"Not in the face!" - Buddy Bizarre
</P>
<P>
"Get your pies for the great pie fight!" - Baker
</P>
<P>
"Taxi!  Drive me off this picture." - Hedley Lamarr
</P>
<P>
"Wow! You shot the bad guy." - Jim
</P>
<P>
"Come on, let's check out the rest of the flick." - Bart
</P>
<P>
"Nowhere special. I always wanted to go there." - Jim
</P>
<P>
