<HEAD>
<TITLE>RAH96: Funny/Useful/Interesting Links</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/grph/rahbkgd.gif">
<CENTER>
<H2>
<IMG SRC="/grph/rah96tm.gif" ALT="Random Access Humor 96 (TM)">
<BR>
Funny/Useful/Interesting Links<BR>
On The Web
</H2>
<P><B>
Warm up your funny bone and don your favorite web-cruising togs -
it's time to seek out some other interesting places on the web.
Just don't forget to save a bookmark or hotlist entry for our
site (<CODE>http://www.rah96.com/</CODE>) and come back to visit
RAH96 regularly!<BR><BR>
This page should be considered under construction at all times.
You never know when things will change. If you know of a funny
and/or interesting/useful site we don't mention here, report it
to the editor: <A HREF="mailto:dave@rah96.com">dave@rah96.com</A>
</B></P>
<BR>
<H3>
Useful/Interesting Spots That Aren't Necessarily Funny
</H3>
<P><B>
Laughter may be the best medicine, but not every worthwhile thing
in this world is funny. Here are some places worth visiting, even
if they don't post the ultimate Dumb Blonde Joke Collection.
</B></P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.stpt.com/">Starting Point</A><BR>
Looking for something on the web? Starting Point lets you metasearch
the major web search databases (e.g. Alta Vista, Yahoo, excite, etc.).
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.altavista.digital.com/">Alta Vista</A><BR>
Dave's favorite web search engine (for the moment, at least).
Alta Vista performs full text searches of web pages for the keyword(s)
you specify.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.wizvax.net/humor/">The Humor Project, Inc.</A>.<BR>
This site looks at the <EM>serious side</EM> of humor. Topics include
humor in stress management, humor in medicine (as used for healing
patients, not a set of drunken doctor jokes), and humor for public
speakers. They have an online catalog of publications available,
and a speakers bureau is said to be on the way.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.minorcon.org/">A Minor Consideration</A><BR>
Many of the best (and funniest) moments in cinema and television history 
have been provided by the performances of children. Most children dream of 
becoming some kind of performer at one time or another. But how many of us 
ever contemplate the cold, hard realities of growing up in the entertainment 
industry?<BR> 
<I>A Minor Consideration</I> (AMC) is a non-profit organization formed to 
give aid and support to child performers - past, present, and future.
AMC was founded by former child actor Paul Petersen (Jeff on the <I>Donna 
Reed Show</I>) in an effort to prevent any repetition of the tragedies that 
have struck down so many former child stars. Mr. Petersen writes with
passion and doesn't sugar coat the facts. If you visit this site, prepare
to have your concept of child stardom changed forever.
</P>
<BR>
<H3>
Funny Stuff: British Comedy/Humor
</H3>
<P><B>
The British may be famous for their "stiff upper lips," but they sure
do know how to make people laugh!
</B></P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://wwwspace.co.uk/andrew/Comedy/">
The British Comedy Library</A><BR>
Andrew Wong's collection of British Comedy FAQs and interviews.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.people.memphis.edu/~jgwright/bladder.htm">
Sup's Blackadder Page</A><BR>
Covers the four historical comedy series featuring everyone's favourite
"lazy, big-nosed, rubber-faced bastard."  Contains pictures and .WAV
files with dialog from the series.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.people.memphis.edu/~jgwright/reddwarf.htm">
Sup's Smegging Red Dwarf Page</A><BR>
Three million years in the future - the mining ship <I>Red Dwarf</I>...
you know all the rest. This site contains cast pictures and .WAV
files with dialog and music from the series.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.ilstu.edu/~dwflore/red-dwarf.guide.html">
Red Dwarf Guide</A>.<BR>
This site contains episode summaries for all six seasons of <I>Red Dwarf</I>.
There are also some strange rumors about the potential seventh season.
</P>
<BR>
<H3>
Funny Stuff: The List of Humo(u)r Site Lists
</H3>
<P><B>
There are literally hundreds of fascinating humor sites on the web.
In order to keep the size of this page down to a reasonable level,
the following list of humor site lists is provided.
</B></P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://a2z.lycos.com/Entertainment_and_Leisure/Humor/">
A2Z Entertainment and Leisure - Humor directory</A><BR>
Lycos maintains the A2Z directory site. The Humor directory lists
many insanely strange sites.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Entertainment/Humor_Jokes_and_Fun/Magazines/">
Yahoo Humor Zine Directory</A>
<BR>
Yahoo maintains a large list of web-based humor zines. They list
RAH96 so their taste is not in question.
</P>
<BR>
<H3>
Funny Stuff: Only On The Web
</H3>
<P><B>
Most sites on the web act as references/indexes to real world
people, places, and things. But there are a few web sites featuring 
activities that are unique to the World Wide Web.  Here are some of 
the funnier ones.
</B></P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.ecst.csuchico.edu/~pizza/">Internet Pizza Server</A><BR>
For those of you who like your pizza with everything, including the
kitchen sink, here is your chance. This virtual pizza parlor offers
toppings ranging from the usual (green peppers, olives, pepperoni,
etc.) to the incredibly unusual (nails, bolts, baseballs, and Curly heads).
These guys are so cocky they've declared war on Pizza Hut!  You can also
<A HREF="pizzadb.html">see a picture of my favorite pizza</A> from this place.
(This site seems to be down quite a bit, but if you keep trying periodically
you should get through eventually.)
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.the-cantina.com/warpath/tidbits/postal/index.html">
It's Time to GO POSTAL!</A>
<BR>
Ever get so fed up with the bullshit of your so-called career and life
that you fondly imagine what it would be like to "go postal" (i.e. bring 
some firearms to work and blow the place, and your co-workers, away)? Yes? 
Then this is the game for you!
</P>
<BR>
<H3>
Funny Stuff: Other
</H3>
<P><B>
Anything that doesn't fit one of the other categories.
</B></P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="rahftp.html">Download The Original RAH Issues</A><BR>
Find out how this all began! Grab one, two, or all 28 of the 
original <I>Random Access Humor</I> issues.  ASCII text editions
in PKZip V2.04 archives.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.misty.com/laughweb/">LaughWEB</A><BR>
Here's where you can find all the Blonde Jokes, Canonical Lists,
and other standard nonsense from the internet. I'm not much for
lists myself, but LaughWEB does have an extensive collection of original
online humor on almost any topic imaginable (and quite a few topics
that aren't readily imaginable).
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.clark.net/silhan/home.html">
Paul Silhan's Parody PARO-DISE</A><BR>
Paul Silhan is the demented person behind many of the hilarious
political parodies heard on Rush Limbaugh's show. Here is where you
can see all his parody lyrics and order Paul's parody albums. Be sure
to check out the "Bob Dole: Mission Possible" spoof! (WARNING: this
site is politically incorrect in the extreme. Close-minded individuals
should avoid it like the truth.)
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://obryan.com/congbillybob">
The More or Less Honorable Billy Bob</A><BR>
Acerbic commentary from the self-elected CyberCongressman from
Western Carolina. (Another bastion of extreme political incorrectness.
Liberals should approach with caution.)
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.sure.net/~joelavin/">
Joe Lavin's Humor Column</A><BR>
So "Generation X" does include some funny (not just funny looking) 
people. Who knew?
</P>
<BR>
<H3>
Funny Stuff: Warner Brothers Animation
</H3>
<P><B>
Keep up with the latest from the best animation studio in history. Just
don't forget to check out the old classics that earned WB that title!
</B></P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.wbanimation.com/">The Official WB Animation Site</A><BR>
This place is actually kind of anemic compared to the unofficial sites
scattered around the web. One particularly bright point: the Acme Hall
of Fame's Bios section. Read about the history of your favorite classic 
Looney Tunes/Merrie Melodies characters.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.usyd.edu.au/~swishart/">Looney Tunes Homepage</A><BR>
A large collection of GIF/JPG pictures and WAV sound files of all the
original Looney Tunes characters. Located in Australia, which is near
Taz's home country.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/brahbul.gif" ALT="">
<A HREF="http://www.uoknor.edu/scs/WILE/">The Wile E. Coyote Question</A><BR>
A great place to check out if you're a Coyote fan and happen to be in
a philosophical mood. This site poses the question, "Is Wile E. Coyote
the greatest cultural icon of our times?" and "If so, why?"  Okay, okay,
that makes two questions. My answer? It just so happens that I have a 
Roadrunner/Coyote poster on the wall of my dining room - a few feet away 
from the Bugs Bunny poster. You figure it out... my shrink has given up.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/rah96bar.gif" ALT="______________________________">
</P>
