<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Poem: Try To Be Me
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#091157 TEXT=#FFFFFF LINK=#FFFF00 VLINK=FF00FF>
<CENTER>
<H2>
Try To Be Me<BR>
by Dave Bealer
</H2>
<P>
Try to be me,<BR>
for just a short while,<BR>
if you'd like to see,<BR>
what makes me smile.
</P>
<P>
Before you criticize me,<BR>
for the things I do,<BR>
put yourself in my place,<BR>
you would do them too.
</P>
<P>
War could be abolished,<BR>
the devil blown away,<BR>
if we could be each other,<BR>
for just one short day.
</P>
<P>
This old world we live in,<BR>
would be a better place,<BR>
if we got under each other's skin,<BR>
wore each other's face.
</P>
<H3>
Copyright &#169; 1977 Dave Bealer, All Rights Reserved.
</H3>
<P>
First rights to this poem were sold to <i>Teens Today</i> back
in 1977. It was Dave's first sale, and probably his first publication.
Since Dave never received his contributor copy, he can't be certain
it was published.
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/grph/davewbar.gif" ALT="______________________________">
</P>
<P>
<BR>
<A HREF="/dave/index.html"><IMG SRC="/grph/homebut.gif" ALT=""></A>
<A HREF="/dave/index.html">Return to Dave's Homepage.</A>
</P>
